      <div class="em-body">
        <div class="em-ornament is-leading">Community Organising</div>
        <p class="em-lead">Emmanuel and St Cuthbert's are members of <a href="https://www.citizensuk.org/about-us/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Citizens UK</a>.</p>
        <p>We partner with local churches, mosques, synagogues, schools, universities and community projects to campaign on issues that concern our communities. North London Citizens campaigns have included: the living wage, youth welfare, support for refugees, and tackling homelessness on our streets.</p>

        <h3>C4WS Night Shelter at Emmanuel</h3>
        <p>From November to February we partner with the charity <a href="https://c4wshomelessproject.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">C4WS</a> to host a weekly night shelter for up to 16 guests who are homeless. Guests arrive in time for a freshly cooked hot meal. They're able to take a hot shower and spend the rest of the evening playing games, chatting, resting or making use of the church wifi.</p>
        <p>We have a team of volunteers who help with the different shifts: set up, prepare the meal, host the evening, and sleeping overnight in the church. If you'd like to get involved, please <a href="contact.html">get in touch with the parish office</a>.</p>

        <h3>Emmanuel Connections</h3>
        <p>Emmanuel Connections is a partnership with Hampstead School, the secondary school in our parish. Through this collaboration, the church community helps to facilitate work experience placements, careers talks and workshops at school, as well as setting up 1-1 mentoring between students and people at different stages of their chosen career.</p>

        <h3>West Hampstead Community Food Hub</h3>
        <p>We have a collection point for the West Hampstead Community Food Hub in both entrances to the church. Food is collected on Fridays and contributes to the WH Foodhub, which runs out of Sidings Community Centre on Saturday mornings. If you would like to support the Foodhub financially or with your time, do <a href="contact.html">get in touch with them directly</a>.</p>

        <h3>Mitzvah Day</h3>
        <p>We are proud to be working in partnership with our friends at Hampstead Synagogue and the JW3 Centre on Finchley Road in collecting for Mitzvah Day each year. We collect food and toiletries for our local food banks in Camden and for the work of the C4WS Winter Night Shelter in Emmanuel Church.</p>
      </div>
